---
import DemoComponentCard from '../../../../components/DemoComponentCard.astro';
---

<p class='text-body-medium'>
  The <code>trigger</code> attribute controls how the popover opens.
  Use <code>click</code> to toggle on click, <code>hover</code> to open on mouse-over,
  or <code>manual</code> to drive visibility programmatically via the <code>open</code> attribute
  or <code>show()</code> / <code>hide()</code> methods.
</p>

<style is:inline>
  .demo-trigger-container .demo-area {
    min-height: 16rem !important;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
</style>

<DemoComponentCard lang='html' cssClasses='demo-trigger-container'>
  <wc-popover trigger='hover'>
    <wc-button variant='tonal'>hover</wc-button>
    <wc-popover-content>Opens on hover</wc-popover-content>
  </wc-popover>

  <wc-popover trigger='click'>
    <wc-button variant='tonal'>click</wc-button>
    <wc-popover-content>Opens on click</wc-popover-content>
  </wc-popover>

  <wc-popover trigger='manual' open>
    <wc-button variant='tonal'>manual (open)</wc-button>
    <wc-popover-content>Manually controlled</wc-popover-content>
  </wc-popover>
</DemoComponentCard>

